cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

The paper focuses on visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of sampling strategies and a novel module for incremental learning, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of benchmarks, which suggests that it falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses long-term tracking and search region strategies, which are common topics in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
